Date: Sat, 14 Aug 93 15:00:08 CST
From: cchen@et.ntit.edu.tw
To: tytso@Athena.MIT.EDU
Subject: console and keyboard stuff


We are studying the Linux console and keyboard related files
but are kind of lost in it.  We wonder if you could point us
to related information to understand the code.  A high level
explanation would also help too.  For example:  what are these
variables supposed to do:
	in console.c
		sel_cons, sel_start, sel_end
		console_blanked
		translations[]
		G0_charset
	in keyboard.c 
		kbd_dead_keys
		key_handler

We can pick up PC related information, but we don't know enough
of the design of keyboard and console handlers to see the workings
of these highly related procedures.  I guess we need pointers to
	1. general description of the design and considerations
		of keyboard and console drivers
	2. Linux specific design description

Thanks for any pointers.

 - Chyouhwa


