Well, since no one else has sent out any information, I guess I should:

For services this Wednesday, we're going to

*** WALDEN POND! *** 

(Yeah, it's great and you can never get to much).
We'll be meeting at the chapel at 5:00 instead of
our normal 5:10, and carpool from there. The service
will be a simple prayer service, followed by a picnic
(bring some food for yourself and to share if you want).

Also, earlier this Wednesday, we'll be having a meeting
of the student planning board. Anyone is welcome to come
with suggestions, opinions, ideas, etc. We'll be meeting
at noon in the Chaplaincy (312 Memorial Drive), and then
decide on a place to go for lunch. (we'll talk and eat at,
well, not quite the same time, but in rapid succession (-; )
If you would like to come, but can't make it on time, we'll
leave a note saying where we went. (It wouldn't hurt to email
me about this either.)

Well, I hope this briefly summarizes what's going on and gives
you enough notice. Feel free to send me questions or even just 
to say hey.

Scott Ramming

