Subject: Minutes of the Network Operations Group Meeting, 16-Aug-93


Minutes of the Network Operations Group Meeting, 16-Aug-93

Present: Jeff, Ted, Tom, Chris, Ron, Kim

Announcements:

	Jeff has another meeting at 2pm, but so we're going make this quick.

	We got the production model of the Safekeeper box from RSA.

	Jeff is at Interop all next week.  

	Jeff is dealing with the Boston Heart Foundation.

Roundtable....

Chris:	[Any news on the repaeter?]  No good news.  The ship dates on
	the MXRI is August 27th and September 3rd.  [ We should push
	on this one, and possibly remind them about the upcoming 
	dormitory order.  :-]

Tom:	The repeater evaluation is proceeding.  We're looking at them now.
	We were really gung-ho of the Asante repeater, but it turns out
	their MAC tracking software doesn't really work.  Then there's
	the cabletron repeater, which stores multiple addresses per port.
	They make work better in our environment.

Chris:	We're should be getting an evaluation unit for the Telebit Netblazer. 
	[ Jeff would like to have something by the end of this quarter.]

Ted:	Is there a cost recovery model yet?  [ Jeff:  Not yet... ]

Jeff:	Next meeting will be in two weeks.  Tom, could you prepare a list
	of repeater vendor embarassing questions?

Next meeting Auguest 30th, 1:30pm.


