----------------------------------------------------------------------------
             	            MarketBase Systems Announces

				       the

			       M a r k e t B a s e (tm)
		         Online Catalog of Goods and Services
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
For Immediate Release

        The MarketBase(tm) Online Catalog of Goods and Services

Santa Barbara, CA - August 16, 1993 - MarketBase Systems today
announced the immediate availability of the MarketBase Online Catalog
of Goods and Services, a unique on-line service dedicated to providing
a forum where buyers and sellers meet to exchange the attributes of
products and services electronically.  FREE access is provided to
product purchasers.

MarketBase provides vendors with a round-the-clock electronic
"store front" where purchasers may browse for goods and services and
instantly access virtually any kind of sales information.

Purchasers are presented with a simple yet powerful series of screens
over a virtual terminal session that requires no specific client or
terminal emulator.  Access is provided via gopher, telnet, ftp, and
dial up modems.  A non-interactive interface will soon be available 
through SMTP (E-mail) for sites that cannot exchange IP with the
Internet in "real-time".

MarketBase gives the gopher user a sophisticated server that allows
customized queries much like what one might expect from a relational
database.

Anyone with a modem or Internet connection can access MarketBase
immediately.  The user interface is simple enough that first-time users
can easily navigate the database and quickly find the product or
service information of interest.  No manuals or training are required.
The interface guides the user from one screen to the next until the
desired product information is delivered.  Complete help is available
at all times through the user interface itself.

Unlike other online product information services, MarketBase is provided
completely FREE OF CHARGE TO PURCHASERS.  Vendors pay a nominal fee to
maintain their product information on MarketBase.

How to Access MarketBase(tm)
----------------------------
1) Internet Gopher.  Point your gopher client at mb.com, port 70.

2) Telneting to MarketBase(tm).  Simply telnet to mb.com.  At the
   "login: " prompt type "mb" followed by a return.

3) Dialup via a data modem.  Set the characteristics of the serial
   port attached to your modem to 8 bits, no parity, and 1 stop bit.
   The number is: (805) 964-3410.  You should get a "login" prompt
   no more than 10 seconds after the modems have finished negotiating
   protocols.

How to register your good or service with MarketBase
----------------------------------------------------
1) Internet Gopher.  Select the "Register Product" item in the root
   menu and follow the prompts.  Or, use your gopher client to mail
   yourself a copy of the registration form from the
   "About MarketBase ..." directory.

2) Send a message to register@mb.com requesting a product registration
   form.  We will send you a form via return E-mail.  Fill in the form(s)
   then E-mail to register@mb.com.

3) Telnet to mb.com.  Log in as user "register".

4) Set your modem to 8N1 and dial up (805) 964-3410.  Log in as user
   "register".

5) FAX requests for or transmit completed product registration forms to
   (805) 964-7430.

6) Send requests for or completed product registration forms to:

    MarketBase Systems
    190 Pebble Hill Drive
    Santa Barbara, CA 93111

INTRODUCTORY OFFER
------------------
For a limited time only, register your good or service on MarketBase
for 30 days at no obligation.  You will be billed only for the 2nd
and succeeding months.

Availability
------------
The gopher, telnet, and dial-up modem interfaces are available
immediately.  The SMTP (E-Mail) and ftp services are expected within
30 days.

Gopher:		mb.com (port 70)
Dial-up:	(805) 964-3410 (8 bits, no parity, 1 stop bit)
General E-mail:	info@mb.com
FAX:		(805) 964-7430
U.S. Mail:	190 Pebble Hill Drive, Santa Barbara, CA  93111

                             * * * * * * * *

MarketBase is a trademark of MarketBase Systems.  All other trademarks
are the property of their respective owners.  All information subject
to change without notice.

