I want to tell you that my problem was resolved.
Yesterday, I called Novutell, a modem company in California.
They faxed me page on how to set modem to com3+irq5. Apparently, I am not the 
only one who needs this information. After set the modem up, I 
remade the kernel (pl11) with one change in 
/usr/src/linux/kernel/chh_drv/serial.c (set irq to 5 for ttyS2).
As you would expect, things work fine. I am very excited. Thank you
very much for the help.
By the way, before remaking the kernel, I used /etc/setserial /dev/cua2 irq 5 
in rc.local. It does NOT work. 



