Announcing "bsd games" version 1.0
----------------------------------

No unix system is truly complete without the traditional bsd games such as
battlestar, canfield, fish, fortune, hangman, mille, robots, wump, etc., etc.

So, not being able to find more than a few of these scattered around,
Andy Tefft and I (Curt Olson) have taken it upon ourselves to port the whole
collection to Linux.  

We have uploaded our initial release to the incoming directories at
tsx-11.mit.edu and sunsite.unc.edu.

They should eventually find their way to 
/pub/linux/source/usr.games/bsd-games.src.tar.gz and 
/pub/linux/binaries/usr.games/bsd-games.bin.tar.gz on tsx-11.mit.edu
and
/pub/Linux/games/[bsd-games.src.tar.gz,bsd-games.bin.tar.gz] on sunsite.unc.edu

