Ted,
  thanks for getting back to me about the invitation for a
goodbye-to-Brian-Sliker dinner for LEM old timers.  It looks
like you returned from Europe a few days after I departed to
Europe (I left on July 26, and you sent an email reply on 
July 29).  I returned last Wednesday evening and read your
email last Thursday.  By that time, I felt it was too late 
to try changing plans (since most people had marked the date
several weeks in advance) and just left it for last Saturday
evening.  Sorry that caused a conflict for your schedule.
We would have enjoyed having you with us, and I regret 
causing you disappointment for having to miss the dinner.
  LEM is still happening every Wednesday.  Please drop in 
when you have time.  Brian has not been coming during the
summer (he spends most of his time down in Quincy, working
on his thesis at home).  We encouraged him to show up at 
least once before he leaves, just so that we can wish him
farewell and he can say farewell to us.  He said he will try
to come some time in September.  I believe that he starts his
new job down in DC early in October. 
  I hope all your work with athena and involvement with your
church in Arlington are going well and not causing too much
stress.
  Hope to see you in the not-too-distant future.

