Barbara discussed this with me, and what she proposes is acceptable 
PROVIDED the machine has a sign on it saying that system accounting is 
turned on, that we will keep all user identities confidential, and 
advising anyone who doesn't want to be accounted to use a different 
workstation. We will need to rediscuss or discontinue the accounting 
when machines become scarce toward the end of term, if the data 
collection goes on that long.

