> I spoke earlier to Richard and Greg Jackson about this, and since I
> received positive responses, I'm going to officially request
> permission to turn on system accounting on one of the test machines
> (preferably test-5000) in the W20-575 athena cluster.  System
> accounting, in essence, keeps a log of every command typed by a user
> on the machine, along with other information such as UID, and CPU
> time.
> 
> Richard, Tom, Christina and I have been investigating the performance
> of a workstation receiving ethernet over a 56 kb line, the setup
> currently being deployed to the ILG's.  We are experimenting with
> different configuration changes (for example, copying parts of the
> system packs locally) to make access faster and easier for residents
> of ILG's.  To accomplish this, we would like to get an idea of which
> programs are used most frequently by the average athena user.  System
> accounting would give us this information. We would not need to look
> at the UIDs associated with each command; we would simply retrieve a
> list of programs run and their relative frequency.
> 
> I would be more than willing to set up accounting myself;  I would
> also post a sign on the machine informing users that system accounting
> was running.  I'd expect to leave system accounting running for about
> a week.
> 
> If you have any questions, you can feel free to email me, or try to 
> find me in e40-342a.
